<item>
            <title>[MATH-1421] WilsonConfidenceInterval returning negative values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1421</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Wilson confidence intervals sometimes return negative values as the lower bound, e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
IntervalUtils.getWilsonScoreInterval(19436, 0, 0.95).getLowerBound() returns -1.3549849074815073E-20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is causing assertion fails in our code, which we have fixed it now by wrapping the confidence score bounds in Math.max(0, Math.min(1, bound)) until the method doesn&apos;t return wrong results anymore.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
